---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '5 May 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Family Friendly UK"
  description="The terms that apply when you use the Family Friendly UK website, including our restaurant-information disclaimer."
>
  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="sep" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span aria-current="page">Terms of Service</span>
      </nav>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section>
    <div class="container legal-prose">
      <p>
        These terms apply when you use Family Friendly UK ("the site"). By using the site you
        agree to these terms. If you don't agree, please don't use the site.
      </p>

      <h2>About the site</h2>
      <p>
        Family Friendly UK is a free directory of family-friendly restaurants across the UK.
        The site is provided as a resource to help parents find places to eat with their
        children. We don't own, operate, or have any commercial relationship with the
        restaurants listed unless we explicitly say otherwise.
      </p>

      <h2>Restaurant information disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        We work hard to keep listings accurate, but information about restaurants — opening
        hours, prices, menus, accessibility, kid-friendly facilities, contact details — can
        change at any time. <strong>The information on this site may not always be up to date.</strong>
        Before you visit a restaurant, especially if you have specific accessibility needs,
        dietary requirements, or are travelling far, please check directly with the restaurant.
      </p>
      <p>
        Restaurant ratings and review counts shown on the site are sourced from publicly
        available data (such as Google) at the time of import and are not updated in real time.
      </p>
      <p>
        Family Friendly UK is not liable for any loss, inconvenience, or disappointment caused
        by inaccurate or out-of-date listing information. Use the site as a starting point, not
        a guarantee.
      </p>

      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>When using the site, you agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the site for any unlawful purpose</li>
        <li>Submit false or misleading restaurant suggestions</li>
        <li>Attempt to scrape, copy, or republish the site or its data without permission</li>
        <li>Interfere with the operation of the site or its security</li>
        <li>Submit spam or other unwanted content through any of our forms</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>User submissions</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit a restaurant suggestion, write to us, or send any other content through
        the site, you grant us permission to review, edit, and (where appropriate) publish it.
        Don't submit anything you don't have the right to share.
      </p>

      <h2>Linked sites</h2>
      <p>
        The site contains links to third-party websites including restaurant websites and
        booking platforms. We don't control those sites and aren't responsible for their
        content, terms, or privacy practices.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The Family Friendly UK name, logo, descriptive text, and the site's design are owned by
        us. You may share short snippets and links to listings for personal, non-commercial
        purposes; please ask before reproducing larger portions of the site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Restaurant names, logos, and trade marks belong to their respective owners. Restaurant
        photographs, where shown, are credited to their original sources.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        The site is provided "as is", with no warranties of any kind. To the fullest extent
        permitted by law, Family Friendly UK is not liable for any indirect, incidental, or
        consequential losses arising out of your use of the site. Nothing in these terms
        excludes liability that cannot lawfully be excluded under English law (such as
        liability for personal injury caused by negligence).
      </p>

      <h2>Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our handling of personal data is described in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. The "Last updated" date above tells you
        when they were last changed. Continued use of the site after a change means you accept
        the new terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any dispute will be subject
        to the non-exclusive jurisdiction of the English courts.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms? Get in touch through the <a href="/suggest">contact form</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal-prose {
  max-width: 760px;
  font-size: 1rem;
  line-height: 1.75;
  color: var(--text);
  padding: 24px 24px 64px;
}
.legal-prose h2 {
  font-family: var(--font-serif);
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  color: var(--green);
  margin: 36px 0 12px;
}
.legal-prose p { margin-bottom: 14px; color: var(--text-muted); }
.legal-prose ul {
  margin: 4px 0 18px 0;
  padding-left: 20px;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}
.legal-prose li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
.legal-prose a { color: var(--green); text-decoration: underline; }
.legal-prose a:hover { color: var(--terracotta); }
</style>
